<svg viewBox="0 0 700 460" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%;height:auto;background:#111113;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);margin:20px 0">
  <text x="20" y="30" fill="#fafafa" font-size="16" font-weight="700" font-family="sans-serif">The Two Faces of Dollar Stablecoins — IMF WP/2026/056 Model</text>
  <text x="20" y="50" fill="#71717a" font-size="12" font-family="sans-serif">Released July 11, 2026 · Author: Brandon Joel Tan</text>
  <rect x="20" y="72" width="660" height="50" rx="8" fill="#18181b" stroke="#3f3f46"/>
  <text x="350" y="93" fill="#e4e4e7" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">Fixed / rationed FX regime (official channel limits dollar supply)</text>
  <text x="350" y="112" fill="#71717a" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">&#8594; gap opens between official and informal (black-market) rate</text>
  <line x1="350" y1="122" x2="350" y2="150" stroke="#f7931a" stroke-width="2"/>
  <polygon points="343,150 357,150 350,162" fill="#f7931a"/>
  <rect x="120" y="164" width="460" height="40" rx="8" fill="#1f1a11" stroke="#92400e"/>
  <text x="350" y="189" fill="#fde68a" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">Dollar stablecoin = liquidity + real-time public price benchmark</text>
  <line x1="230" y1="204" x2="150" y2="232" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="2"/>
  <line x1="470" y1="204" x2="550" y2="232" stroke="#f87171" stroke-width="2"/>
  <rect x="20" y="236" width="280" height="94" rx="8" fill="#0f1f18" stroke="#15803d"/>
  <text x="35" y="260" fill="#bbf7d0" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">Wider access (normal times)</text>
  <text x="35" y="282" fill="#a7f3d0" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Unbanked/capped individuals &amp; firms</text>
  <text x="35" y="300" fill="#a7f3d0" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">can still hold/transfer dollars</text>
  <text x="35" y="318" fill="#a7f3d0" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">e.g. Bolivia, Argentina commerce</text>
  <rect x="400" y="236" width="280" height="94" rx="8" fill="#1f1315" stroke="#7f1d1d"/>
  <text x="415" y="260" fill="#fecaca" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="700">Faster exit (crisis times)</text>
  <text x="415" y="282" fill="#fca5a5" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Single public price = coordination device</text>
  <text x="415" y="300" fill="#fca5a5" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Individual &#8594; simultaneous currency exit</text>
  <text x="415" y="318" fill="#fca5a5" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Echoes Diamond-Dybvig bank-run structure</text>
  <rect x="20" y="346" width="660" height="60" rx="8" fill="#18181b" stroke="#3f3f46"/>
  <text x="350" y="368" fill="#e4e4e7" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="13" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">IMF proposal: temporary caps on unusually large, panic-driven transfers</text>
  <text x="350" y="388" fill="#71717a" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle">Aims to dampen the synchronized-exit signal without blocking access itself</text>
  <text x="20" y="428" fill="#71717a" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Cases: Bolivia airport USDT pricing (Jun 9, 2025), Argentina informal peso-stablecoin networks (2024)</text>
  <text x="20" y="446" fill="#71717a" font-family="sans-serif" font-size="12">Source: IMF Working Paper WP/2026/056, Cointelegraph, CoinTribune</text>
</svg>
</div>
